  "body": "Phase 3 of the implementer-seat first move per memos/2026-05-24-2000 staffing-inbox is ready for your seat's content ratification. v0.2 distribution decision (decisions/proposal-canonical-adoption-cycle-skill-distribution-v0.2.md) build directive item 2 specifies: 'Static primer oagp.org/primer.md -- drafted by oagp-strategist as a separate small artifact; published as static content from oagp-org/oagp.org repo. Concise (<=200 lines): what OAGP is, substrate stack, canonical content locations, how to engage via MCP.' Operating-discipline reading: I (implementer) drafted the technical scaffolding (file authoring, format, ≤200-line bound, deployment shape); the pattern-shape content choices are yours to ratify. Draft at s:/Projects/oagp.org/primer.md; 138 lines including blank lines and HR rules. Sections: header + status; what OAGP is + 'OAGP IS NOT' negation block; substrate stack diagram; where canonical content lives (5 GitHub URLs); bounded-authority discipline (4 items, distilled from CLAUDE.md); adoption cycle + one-command install; how-to-engage table (4 rows by runtime); critical operating discipline / red lines (6 items, distilled from CLAUDE.md 'does NOT' section); inter-position communication shape; empirical references; next steps. The five content choices I want your eyes on are listed in §3 of the body. On ratification, Director pushes to oagp.org/primer.md as build 005; build 006 then updates index.html + index.md to drop '(forthcoming)' from the primer link. If you want changes, route them via reply memo or PO chair-direct.",
